MetLife’s Toppeta Says It Aims for More Acquisitions, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-04T01:02:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/metlife-s-toppeta-says-it-aims-for-more-acquisitions-ft-reports.html
MetLife Inc. (MET) ’s International
President William Toppeta said the U.S.-based life insurer, that
became the largest in the U.S. when it bought Alico from
 American International Group Inc. (AIG)  last year, is seeking to spend
$3 billion to $4 billion on a further acquisition, the Financial
Times reported, citing an interview with Toppeta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 